"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1a032a",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Erysipelas or cellulitis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e8bf68",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Mild: Oral penicillin, cephalosporin, dicloxacillin, clindamycin"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3220f6",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Moderate: Intravenous penicillin, ceftriaxone, cefazolin, clindamycin",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"27ad5e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Severe: Surgical assessment for possible necrotizing component and empiric intravenous vancomycin plus piperacillin-tazobactam, imipenem, or meropenem"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f32286",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Necrotizing fasciitis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ca9b74",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Polymicrobial infection: Surgical assessment/debridement and combination therapy such as vancomycin plus piperacillin-tazobactam or imipenem or meropenem"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6c64e5",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Streptococcus pyogenes"
]
},
" or ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Clostridium"
]
},
" species: Surgical assessment/debridement and penicillin plus clindamycin"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4db2b2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Aeromonas hydrophila"
]
},
": Surgical assessment/debridement and ciprofloxacin plus doxycycline"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9fb7da",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Vibrio vulnificus"
]
},
": Surgical assessment/debridement and ceftazidime, ceftriaxone, or cefotaxime plus doxycycline"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0a5fda",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Folliculitis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9c1da2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Staphylococcus aureus"
]
},
": Usually self-limited; can use topical mupirocin, clindamycin, or retapamulin; systemic antibiotics usually not needed"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c8d963",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Pseudomonas aeruginosa"
]
},
" (i.e., hot tub folliculitis): Usually self-limited; oral ciprofloxacin usually reserved for immunosuppressed host or for persistent or severe infection"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-4 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f5a804",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Furuncle, carbuncle, or abscess"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"92b31c",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Mild: Incision and drainage; consider adjunctive oral anti-MRSA antibiotic like trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"507813",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Moderate: Incision and drainage plus empiric trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole or doxycycline pending culture and susceptibilities"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"03aeda",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Severe: Incision and drainage plus empiric vancomycin, daptomycin, linezolid, telavancin, or ceftaroline pending culture and susceptibilities"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
}
]
},
